cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing (NLP) tasks such as Disease Named Entity Recognition (Disease-NER). It also uses Deep Learning (DL) models which are commonly used in NLP tasks. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as DL models are a subset of Machine Learning. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as DL models are a subset of AI and the paper deals with DL models for NLP tasks. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as DL models are based on neural networks. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with extracting disease Named Entities (NEs) from text, which is a task related to information retrieval.
